<subSubSection id="8156540135B1FE7A5ECF49512E3CA1C8" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="taxonomic notes">
<paragraph id="C51E21E7C6A007BFDA533FB44437954E" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EA968121C8484792A01F188E9E6DA2D6" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
<bibRefCitation id="8439C5BABA5D36A0C2E3A786A4897CED" author="Grau, J" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Botanischen Staatssammlung Muenchen" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="111 - 203" refId="B12" refString="Grau, J, Gronbach, E, 1984. Untersuchungen zur Variabilitaet in der Gattung Schizanthus (Solanaceae). Mitteilungen der Botanischen Staatssammlung Muenchen 20: 111 - 203" title="Untersuchungen zur Variabilitaet in der Gattung Schizanthus (Solanaceae)." volume="20" year="1984">Grau and Gronbach (1984</bibRefCitation>
: 147) erroneously accepted as the first valid publication of this species that of 
<bibRefCitation id="DBA9D8C6B6B23FFCD962A2515D522D42" author="Bentham, G" editor="de Candolle, AP" journalOrPublisher="V. Masson, Paris" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="186 - 586" refId="B3" refString="Bentham, G, 1846. Scrophulariaceae. In: de Candolle, AP, Ed., Prodromus Systematis Naturalis Regni Vegetabilis 10. V. Masson, Paris: 186 - 586" title="Scrophulariaceae." volumeTitle="Prodromus Systematis Naturalis Regni Vegetabilis 10." year="1846">Bentham (1846)</bibRefCitation>
. Consequently, they chose as a type a specimen from G-DC, linking it to the original publication. Regarding this matter, it is important to say that we have not seen this specimen, as it is not available at Global Plants JSTOR (https://plants.jstor.org/) or at the herbarium catalogue of the institution (http://www.ville-ge.ch/musinfo/bd/cjb/chg/). 
<taxonomicName id="E3FAD0D15419FBFCD3A9DECC886B5076" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Schizanthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Schizanthus alpestris" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alpestris">
<emphasis id="F84379FAD26E9ACF3217F91090A72793" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Schizanthus alpestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described and validly published almost 20 years earlier by 
<bibRefCitation id="A55516ADE928BE8BA7AFC80CF6767BBC" author="Poeppig, E" journalOrPublisher="Notizen aus dem Gebiete der Natur-und Heikunde" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="289 - 293" refId="B37" refString="Poeppig, E, 1829. Edreiben des jekt in Chile reifenben Srn. Dr. Poeppig. Notizen aus dem Gebiete der Natur-und Heikunde 503: 289 - 293" title="Edreiben des jekt in Chile reifenben Srn. Dr. Poeppig." volume="503" year="1829">Poeppig (1829)</bibRefCitation>
. Hence, the type cited by 
<bibRefCitation id="6E1940613DC50B0A4ECBBC7F509FED5B" author="Grau, J" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Botanischen Staatssammlung Muenchen" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="111 - 203" refId="B12" refString="Grau, J, Gronbach, E, 1984. Untersuchungen zur Variabilitaet in der Gattung Schizanthus (Solanaceae). Mitteilungen der Botanischen Staatssammlung Muenchen 20: 111 - 203" title="Untersuchungen zur Variabilitaet in der Gattung Schizanthus (Solanaceae)." volume="20" year="1984">Grau and Gronbach (1984)</bibRefCitation>
is not that of 
<normalizedToken id="2A069CCCE9C9705EB9FA43F5F2045D77" originalValue="Poeppigâs">Poeppig's</normalizedToken>
name.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FCBE3B93AC57F5BCAB4B3ABE56A165F0" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
<bibRefCitation id="98D0FFD6F7ED2C293CF6706FDFD1A3D2" author="Poeppig, E" journalOrPublisher="Notizen aus dem Gebiete der Natur-und Heikunde" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="289 - 293" refId="B37" refString="Poeppig, E, 1829. Edreiben des jekt in Chile reifenben Srn. Dr. Poeppig. Notizen aus dem Gebiete der Natur-und Heikunde 503: 289 - 293" title="Edreiben des jekt in Chile reifenben Srn. Dr. Poeppig." volume="503" year="1829">Poeppig (1829)</bibRefCitation>
does not mention a type specimen or a specific area of collection, but the title of his work refers to collections made at 
<normalizedToken id="D27551C49AC322CD2386FD6A2455CE96" originalValue="RÃ­o">Rio</normalizedToken>
Colorado in the Andes of Chile and being gathered by him on 24th of December of 1827. We have found two specimens that can be related to this trip, but none of them are part of the Poeppig herbaria at W or at B and LE, where his samples were distributed by G. Kunze (
<bibRefCitation id="6F1A7D4693DE991298294E2DCBC0A534" author="Stafleu, FA" journalOrPublisher=", Publisher, The Hague / Boston" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" refId="B50" refString="Stafleu, FA, Cowan, RS, 1983. Taxonomic Literature. A selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types (2nd ed.). Volume IV: P-Sak. Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema, Utrecht &amp; dr. W Junk b.v., Publisher, The Hague/Boston" title="Taxonomic Literature. A selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types (2 nd ed.). Volume IV: P-Sak. Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema, Utrecht &amp; dr. W Junk b. v." year="1983">Stafleu and Cowan 1983</bibRefCitation>
). However, the sheets at HAL [135744] and P [P00477033] have a printed label, where the original publication is mentioned (Not. XXIII); these were distributed after Poeppig described the species. Hence, we think these samples are part of the material used in the description, and thus original material. As no holotype is mentioned in the description and we found two specimens referring to the same collection, a lectotypification is made here. Our selection of the lectotype was based on the best-preserved specimen that shows the morphological characters of the species and the full locality data. According to the printed label on the specimens, the material was collected at the confluence of the rivers Colorado and Chille. The latter corresponds to an old name for the Aconcagua River (
<bibRefCitation id="90D93BC21073BE5D9639D8FF7E7D9053" author="Risopatron, L" journalOrPublisher="Imprenta Universitaria, Santiago de Chile" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" refId="B39" refString="Risopatron, L, 1924. Diccionario Jeografico de Chile. Imprenta Universitaria, Santiago de Chile" title="Diccionario Jeografico de Chile." year="1924">
<normalizedToken id="1AFF7B7F8C32613CACF515EE261863C7" originalValue="RisopatrÃ³n">Risopatron</normalizedToken>
1924
</bibRefCitation>
), area which agrees with the currently known distribution of the species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B30EA2DC7611C3C6D0B49EBCBE8B2ED7" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
A further two specimens collected by Poeppig were not considered as type material because of the following reasons: the locality cited on the specimen at P [P00477034] is insufficient to be linked to the protologue (&quot; 
<emphasis id="0E8034BFDEDF4994FF39D021208F8565" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Chile boreal. Andes.</emphasis>
&quot;). On the other hand, the specimen at F [875198] has two labels: one of them contains the locality and date of collection (&quot; 
<emphasis id="813C615FF8EDFBDA53C952A8EAF79151" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Andes de Sa. Rosa. Chile. 1828</emphasis>
&quot;), data which do not agree the protologue. A second label refers to two different numbers given to the species on 
<normalizedToken id="849E6E08F185239D6AE512373D6A91C7" originalValue="Poeppigâs">Poeppig's</normalizedToken>
diary (&quot; 
<emphasis id="9AAD1AAA7D5637E4BDD29371A2179FEE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
NÂ° 12. 
<taxonomicName id="8B93FDA312F2D2E3106103B73B8D03FE" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Schizanthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Schizanthus alpestris" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alpestris">Schizanthus alpestris</taxonomicName>
Pg. Diar. 562. A.
</emphasis>
&quot;). Those numbers are not to be associated to numbers of collection, which is different.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="85F1F07D1E50DCD3911A274B5EE6B31F" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="key">
<paragraph id="5524C1C879CCB9D9309B6C677BE29DED" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Key characters.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DE4D817C5BCD10FC2F835E718EA2D619" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Delicate small flowers (14-18 mm long, 14-16 mm wide), external portion of the corolla lavender or lilac, upper middle corolla lobe narrowly oblong, with a bilobed apex, sometimes these lobes a little divided.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4931D1048944700FA7DB3CB1DAC5B96B" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="6F3399353191C5A0DCA45DE6FF88C6D3" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="68077D88FA9612714743E2CF364810D3" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
Endemic to Chile, between the Regions of Atacama (Province of Huasco, 28Â°50' lat. S) and 
<normalizedToken id="DB17613E21EA52952695F1DB45C38D5C" originalValue="ValparaÃ­so">Valparaiso</normalizedToken>
(Province of Los Andes, 32Â°50' lat. S). 180-2800 m a.s.l.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C15E39C079530F225F4F05621662C7B8" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="habitat">
<paragraph id="757706536C2D91A05BBA3DB82395A4C0" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9C8A8350CE3DB2FD5888CD021282488A" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
<taxonomicName id="5A944DDD3E37A1B2969D11F37627FF5F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Schizanthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Schizanthus alpestris" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alpestris">
<emphasis id="858934A3A54453B9C0823E05DCFBD066" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Schizanthus alpestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is abundant on stony hillsides, along railroads, roadsides, and watercourses; among rocks over loose soil. It has also been found in rocky areas, where it seems to be scarce. In these rocky areas, it grows with 
<taxonomicName id="8C3C87192D66E2F8E9903D37B6EEC83E" authorityName="Molina" authorityYear="1782" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Puya" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Puya" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E88D9A86C9B05138A67B94FEF9B7A8B4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Puya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. (
<taxonomicName id="CE6F98A6C7DF48264100FC0508AA9181" authorityName="Molina" authorityYear="1782" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Puya" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Bromeliaceae</taxonomicName>
